PrintSetupJPEGQuality Property

Requires: Base Development System

Class: Application Properties (ActiveX)

Percentage value from 0 to 100 specifying the level of quality you want for the JPEG graphic in VIs printed either interactively or with the PrintVIToHTML method. The scale balances image quality and file size. A value in the 75-95 range produces a compressed file with a high-quality image, and a value below 50 produces a smaller file size with a low-quality image. The default is 80.

Syntax

object.PrintSetupJPEGQuality

Data Type

long
